This paper discusses a method to authenticate parties to counter man-in-the-middle (MIM) attack that can jeopardize the double-lock cryptography protocol. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and cryptography (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the implementation of the method, which involves information theory (cs.IT), software engineering (cs.SE), and computer engineering (cs.CE).
